cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.GT 

The paper discusses resource management issues in non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) networks, which are a key technology for 5G and beyond. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses power-domain and code-domain NOMA, which are related to information theory and communication systems, respectively, suggesting cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) as likely categories. The paper also presents a game-theoretic framework for resource management, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
